<br>
Unfortunately, there is a Rogue NPC in the Foreign Quarter who can see through illusions (last I remember there was. Has this changed?). If he can see through mask illusions, I'm sure he can see through a potion one as well, but it's worth a shot if you're that adamant about it. <br>
<br>
Good luck!<br>
<br>
By the way, this is the ONLY thing I've found where you can RAISE faction with The Spurned. <br>
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
<br>
Starts in: Neriak 3rd Gate <br>
Who: Ithvol K`Jasn <br>
Rating: Average (3.96) <br>
Estimated Time: 5 hours <br>
Minimum Level: 13 <br>
Maximum Level: 65 <br>
Best Class: Cler Sham <br>
Factions Raised:<br>
Dread Guards Outer<br>
King Naythox Thex<br>
Priests of Innoruk<br>
The Spurned<br>
 <br>
Factions Lowered:<br>
Clerics of Tunare<br>
Priests of Life<br>
Priests of Marr<br>
The Dead<br>
 <br>
Quest Items:<br>
Initiate Symbol of Innoruuk<br>
 <br>
Additional Zones:<br>
Nektulos Forest<br>
Neriak 3rd Gate<br>
Neriak Commons<br>
West Commonlands<br>
 <br>
Related Creatures:<br>
Draxiz N'Rit<br>
Ithvol K`Jasn<br>
Leatherfoot Spy<br>
Master Whoopal<br>
Quester Dunden<br>
Wallin Slyfoot<br>
 <br>
Related Quests:<br>
Innoruuk Initiate<br>
Innoruuk Regent<br>
 <br>
Submitted by: Slayne <br>
This is done after completing the initiate quest. <br>
<br>
Hail Ithvol K'Jasn and tell him 'I am an initiate'. He will tell you to go and slay Master Whoopal in Nektulos and take his head to Draxiz in the The Tower of the Spurned. (Master Whopal spawns at a Totem Pole just west of the bridge near the shore. His placeholder if Questor Dunden.) Slay him and you will get a Halfling Head. <br>
<br>
Return to Neriak Commons and give the head to Draxiz. He will give you a mask, which looks like a head, that will give you 1 guise of halfling. <br>
<br>
Now head down to West Commons and look for an npc halfling called Wallin Slyfoot. He wanders a bit, but usually ends up on the path near Kitchor. When you find him active the illusion spell and tell him that you will assist him and he will give you a letter for Master Whopal (Hehe..he's dead) <br>
<br>
Now return to Neriak Commons and give Draxiz this note. This will cause the Leatherfoot spies to spawn. They spawn in a small room behind the waterfall near the PoD. Kill them (there may be two) and one of them will drop another Halfling Head. <br>
<br>
Return to Neriak 3rd Gate and take this head and your Initiate Symbol to Ithvol. He will reward you with your Disciple Symbol <br>
<br>
Note: Dealing with Draxis will lower your Dead Faction. It is a small hit but if you are Dub, then think twice before doing this part. <br>
Reward(s): <br>
Disciple Symbol of Innoruuk<br>
Skinned Halfling Face Mask<br>
<br>
